name: Real Mechanical Parts
description:
v1.2;

+Added more variations into mechanical parts.

+Hopefuly fixed issues where collides some of other loras.

+learning rate changed so it will snap into object more natural than the older version.

  • use reelmech tag and if you want almost full mechanical parts use it with 1.5 ratio such as this (reelmech:1.5)

v.1.0;

This is my first Lora model that is aimed for mechanical parts for organic bodies. Mostly humanoids.

I've tried it on more than 5 popular checkpoints and it worked fine but with 1 flaw. If you don't upscale at least x2 ( two times ) you will most likely get blurry faces. If you do upscale, you won't get any problems with faces.

Use lora tag <lora:reelmech:1>

also add a method, (mechanical parts:1.x) where x is equal to a number to increase number of mechanical parts on your model. I recommend it to set that number between 1.1 to 1.5.

If you leave a comment, i can make it better models of me and your liking!

I appreciate it if you support and buy me coffee.
